  <other_name type="common_name">Point Reyes meadowfoam</other_name>
  <discussion type="conservation">of conservation concern;</discussion>
  <discussion>Subspecies sulphurea is easily recognized by its entirely yellow petals. It is known only from Point Reyes, Marin County, and the Butano Creek area, San Mateo County (R. Ornduff 1971).</discussion>
